---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | LogicLoom Systems" description="How we handle your data.">
    <section class="py-32 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
            <p>Last updated: December 17, 2025</p>
            <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
            <p>LogicLoom Systems ("we", "our", "us") respects your privacy. This policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our website and services.</p>
            <h3>2. Data Collection</h3>
            <p>We collect information you provide directly to us (e.g., when booking a call or filling out an audit form). This may include your name, email, and business details.</p>
            <h3>3. Use of Data</h3>
            <p>We use your data to: Provide our automation services, communicate with you about your projects, and send invoices.</p>
            <h3>4. Data Security</h3>
            <p>We implement industry-standard security measures. For n8n deployments, your data resides on your private server infrastructure.</p>
            <h3>5. Contact</h3>
            <p>Questions? Email us at hello@logicloomsystems.com</p>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>